---------------
MAYS AMIGA NEWS
---------------

Amiga.org News Disgrace
The Amiga.org news database was disgracefully hacked in the early days
of this month. Hackers, who I believe aren't Amiga fans, got very close
to destroying Amiga.org's reputation by hacking the database and posting
an offensive mail about the Amiga and the excellent Miami. Thanks to
the Amiga.org teams' quick action, the messages were removed and a prompt
apology posted on to the site.

Trogsoft Looking for CGI
We're looking for people who can write Perl CGI scripts for our site to
do things. In particular we'll be wanting a page where people can add
links, a form emailer script, and a number of scripts which we'll
tell you about when we think of them. Want to apply? Send an email
to trogladite@trogsoft.freeserve.co.uk

Rebol for PPC
Looks like the Rebol team (you know, Carl Sassenrath etc. :) are going
to be making a version of Rebol for the PPC powered Amiga. Good eh? :)
Check out www.rebol.com

Amiga Inc. Presence
Amiga Inc. will be present at Amiwest (in the United States) and
World Of Amiga 99 (no relation :). So expect some sort of announcement
and don't forget we'll have a report from WOA99 next issue.

Video Titling
Extreme 1.5 is now available. It can calculate backgrounds in realtime
and is perfect for all you video titling people out there. Check out
www.idealia.net/darkage/extreme.html

AAA Awards Now Open
Yep, this years annual AA Awards are open for voting. This year, the
UK nominees are Ben Vost (Amiga Format Editor), Neil Bothwick (of
Amiga ISP Wirenet) and Chris Wiles of Active Technologies.
www.aaa-awards.org   - vote and you could win lots of prizes!!!

